            "content": [
              {
                "type": "output_text",
                "text": "Here are the latest updates on London Underground service disruptions:\n\n1. **Line Closures**: There are closures affecting the Piccadilly, Northern, Metropolitan, and Elizabeth lines this weekend. Notably, there will be:\n   - No service between Harrow-on-the-Hill and Uxbridge on the Metropolitan line and Acton Town to Uxbridge on the Piccadilly line on December 5-7.\n   - No service on sections of the Northern line between Archway and High Barnet after 5:30 AM on December 6-7.\n   - Early morning closures on the Elizabeth line between Paddington and Ealing Broadway on December 7 [Yahoo News UK](https://uk.news.yahoo.com).\n\n2. **Christmas and New Year**: Most TfL services will operate as usual over the festive period, but there are planned closures. \n   - No service on Christmas Day, and early finishes on Christmas Eve.\n   - Boxing Day will see reduced services and some closures, including on the DLR and Elizabeth line [Transport for London](https://tfl.gov.uk).\n\n3. **Strike Impact**: No planned industrial action affecting TfL services, but it's advised to monitor updates in case of changes [Greater Anglia](https://www.greateranglia.co.uk).\n\nFor the latest and real-time updates, it's recommended to use the TfL website or TfL Go app ahead of your travel plans.",
